        <num>CC 1297</num>
        <heading>1297.  Stipulations against partition</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1297.  Stipulations against partition.
It can not be stipulated that there never shall be a partition of a succession or of a thing held in common.  Such a stipulation would be null and of no effect.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
